<!--
    PUF France Use Case 7: Invoice Following Purchase Paid with Corporate Card
    (Facture suite à achat payé par carte logée)
    
    Business Scenario:
    - Employee books hotel room for business trip
    - Payment made with company corporate purchase card
    - Card manager pays hotel directly
    - Hotel issues already-paid invoice to company
    - Company reconciles invoice with card statement
    - Company pays monthly statement to card manager
    
    Key Requirements:
    - Business process B2: Already-paid invoice
    - BT-113 (Prepaid amount): Equal to BT-112 (card manager paid full amount)
    - BT-115 (Amount due): 0 (nothing owed to seller)
    - NO third-party PAYER block (purchase card is BUYER's payment means, not separate payer)
    - BT-87 (Card account number): Last 4-6 digits MANDATORY
    - BT-88 (Cardholder name): Optional
    - Payment means code: 48 (Bank card)
    
    Financial Breakdown:
    - Hotel room: 180.00 EUR (net)
    - VAT 10% (lodging reduced rate): 18.00 EUR
    - Total with VAT: 198.00 EUR
    - Corporate card paid: 198.00 EUR (full amount to hotel)
    - Amount due to seller: 0.00 EUR
    - Company will pay card manager via monthly statement
    
    Workflow:
    1. Employee books hotel with corporate card
    2. Card manager pays hotel (198.00 EUR)
    3. Hotel creates e-invoice to COMPANY (already paid)
    4. Company receives invoice via PPF platform
    5. Company reconciles invoice with card statement
    6. Company pays monthly statement to card manager
    
    French Text Codes (BT-21/BT-22):
    - #REG#: Company legal form and share capital
    - #ABL#: Trade register number (RCS)
    - #AAI#: APE business activity code
    - #PMD#: Late payment penalties
    - #PMT#: Fixed collection costs indemnity (€40)
    - #BAR#: Treatment type (B2B e-invoicing)
    - #PAI#: Third party payment information (corporate card payment via card manager)
-->
